The present disclosure will be more fully understood from the description of the following examples, which, however, should not be taken to limit the invention to any specific embodiment but are for purposes of explanation and to provide a better understanding of the disclosed apparatus and method. The examples may be better understood with reference to the following figures:
Fig.1 is a functional block diagram of a multi-antenna transceiver system which includes elements suitable for implementing the disclosed method;
Fig. 2 is a more detailed block diagram of a transceiver that includes a signal processor capable of executing a set of instructions for implementing the disclosed method;
Fig. 3 is a block diagram illustrating a strategy computation method and apparatus that uses estimates of one or more characteristic features of a first set of data;
Fig. 4 is a block diagram illustrating a reference signal generator that may be used in any of the embodiments herein described;
Fig. 5 is a block diagram illustrating modification of the method and apparatus of Fig. 3 according to one embodiment;
Fig. 6 is a block diagram illustrating a further modification the method and apparatus of Fig. 3 illustrating some of the signal processing operations applied to received data when implementing an embodiment;
Fig. 7 is a block diagram illustrating an example method applied to a covariance based processing strategy;
Fig. 8 is a block diagram illustrating some of the signal processing operations applied to received data when implementing yet another example method;
Fig. 9 is a block diagram illustrating some of the signal processing operations applied to received data when implementing yet another example method;
Fig.10 is a block diagram illustrating some of the signal processing operations applied to received data when implementing an example method applied to a noise-plus-interference covariance based processing strategy;
Fig. 11 is a block diagram showing a strategy computation method and apparatus having as input a first set of data and a reference signal for the first set of data;
Fig. 12 is a block diagram showing modification of the method and apparatus of Fig.11 according to an aspect of the present disclosure;
Fig. 13 is a block diagram showing a signal injection based example method applied to processing strategy;
Fig. 14 is a block diagram showing a synthetic signal injection feature-extraction example method applied to a processing strategy;
Fig. 15 is a block diagram showing an example method applied to a processing strategy generator which uses a reference signal, primary data, and a covariance estimate, with the covariance estimate modified by signal injection to include the interference mitigating effects of the secondary signal;
Fig. 16 is a block diagram showing application of a signal-injection example of the disclosed method to a processing strategy generator which uses a reference signal, primary data, and a noise-plus-interference covariance estimator;
Fig. 17 is a block diagram showing a signal-injection example of the disclosed method applied to a non-linear strategy generator, where the strategy generator includes a demodulation stage;
Fig. 18 is a block diagram showing a general application of a signal-injection example of the disclosed method as used to process tertiary data;
Fig. 19 is a comparison of the performance of a prior art uplink weight determining method with a method according to one example, and shows the effect of varying the of the desired user while keeping the ratio of powers of the user and interferer (the C/I ratio or CIR) constant; and
Fig. 20 is another comparison of the performance of a prior art uplink weight determining method with a method according to one example, and shows the effect of varying the C/I ratio while keeping the SNR of the desired user constant.

claim.claim-text:
A method in a remote unit, the method comprising:
transmitting, via a channel, a first signal to an adaptive array antenna system (103), wherein the first signal embodies primary data (Fig. 3), and wherein the first signal further embodies a reference signal (Fig. 4), which enables the adaptive array antenna system (103) to analyse the reference signal and, based on analysis of the reference signal, establish a set of transmit and receive weights for communicating with the remote unit;
transmitting, via the channel, a second signal (Fig. 5) to the adaptive array antenna system (103) for which a reference signal is not available;
and receiving, via the channel, a downlink signal from the adaptive array antenna system (103), wherein the received downlink signal incorporates updated transmit and receive weights for communicating with the remote unit, the updated transmit and receive weights derived by the adaptive array antenna system (103) based on primary data Z1 derived by the adaptive array antenna system (103) from the first signal and further based on secondary data Z2 derived by the adaptive array antenna system (103) from the second signal, the updated transmit and receive weights for communicating with the remote unit applied to the downlink signal by the adaptive array antenna system (103) to alter antenna beamforming and nullforming characteristics of an array of antenna elements of the adaptive array antenna system (103) to account for a presence of a changing interference environment.

An article of manufacture comprising a machine-accessible medium that includes content that when accessed provides instruction to cause a remote unit to implement a method comprising:
transmitting, via a channel, a first signal to an adaptive array antenna system (103), wherein the first signal embodies primary data (Fig. 3), and wherein the first signal further embodies a reference signal (Fig. 4), which enables the adaptive array antenna system to analyse the reference signal and, based on analysis of the reference signal, establishe a set of transmit and receive weights for communicating with the remote unit;
transmitting, via the channel, a second signal (Fig. 5) to the adaptive array antenna system (103) for which a reference signal is not available;
and receiving, via the channel, a downlink signal from the adaptive array antenna system (103), wherein the received downlink signal incorporates updated transmit and receive weights for communicating with the remote unit, the updated transmit and receive weights derived by the adaptive array antenna system (103) based on the first signal and further based on the second signal, wherein the updated transmit and receive weights for communicating with the remote unit are incorporated into the downlink signal by the adaptive array antenna system (103) to alter antenna beamforming and nullforming characteristics of the adaptive array antenna system (103) to account for the presence of a changing interference environment.

A wireless remote unit comprising:
a transmitter to transmit, via a channel, a first signal to an adaptive array antenna system (103), wherein the first signal embodies primary data (Fig. 3), and wherein the first signal further embodies a reference signal (Fig. 4), which enables the adaptive array antenna system (103) to analyse the reference signal and, based on analysis of the reference signal, establishe a set of transmit and receive weights for communicating with the wireless remote unit;
the transmitter to further transmit, via the channel, a second signal (Fig. 5) to the adaptive array antenna system (103) for which a reference signal is not available;
and a receiver to receive, via the channel, a downlink signal from the adaptive array antenna system (103), wherein the received downlink signal incorporates updated transmit and receive weights for communicating with the wireless remote unit, the updated transmit and receive weights derived by the adaptive array antenna system (103) based on the first signal and further based on the second signal, wherein the updated transmit and receive weights for communicating with the wireless remote unit are incorporated into the downlink signal by the adaptive array antenna system (103) to alter antenna beamforming and nullforming characteristics of the adaptive array antenna system (103) to account for the presence of a changing interference environment.

Unité distante sans fil comprenant :
un émetteur destiné à transmettre, par l'intermédiaire d'un canal, un premier signal à un système (103) d'antennes en réseau adaptatives, dans lequel le premier signal intègre des données primaires (figure 3), et dans lequel le premier signal intègre en outre un signal de référence (figure 4), ce qui permet au système (103) d'antennes en réseau adaptatives d'analyser le signal de référence, et, sur la base de l'analyse du signal de référence, d'établir un ensemble de pondérations d'émission et de réception en vue de communiquer avec l'unité distante sans fil ;
l'émetteur est en outre destiné à transmettre, par l'intermédiaire du canal, un second signal (figure 5) au système (103) d'antennes en réseau adaptatives pour lequel un signal de référence n'est pas disponible ;
et un récepteur destiné à recevoir, par l'intermédiaire du canal, un signal de liaison descendante en provenance du système (103) d'antennes en réseau adaptatives, dans lequel le signal de liaison descendante reçu intègre des pondérations d'émission et de réception mises à jour en vue de communiquer avec l'unité distante sans fil, les pondérations d'émission et de réception mises à jour étant déduites par le système (103) d'antennes en réseau adaptatives sur la base du premier signal et en outre sur la base du second signal, dans lequel les pondérations d'émission et de réception mises à jour en vue de communiquer avec l'unité distante sont intégrées dans le signal de liaison descendante par le système (103) d'antennes en réseau adaptatives en vue de modifier des caractéristiques de formation de zéro et de formation de faisceau d'antenne du système (103) d'antennes en réseau adaptatives afin de tenir compte de la présence d'un environnement à interférences variables.
